---
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---
<PageLayout title="About Our School">
  <div class="prose-bfs">
    <h2>Our Story</h2>
    <p>
      Bright Futures began as a small charity in 2007. It was created by a group of parents who were seeking improvements to the quality and range of services for children with autism. In March 2010, Bright Futures secured a 'start-up' grant to develop 'special school' provision.
    </p>
    <p>
      In March 2011, the new school underwent a successful 'material change' Ofsted inspection with the outcome that Bright Futures School was registered with the DfE as a special school for children with autism.
    </p>
    <p>
      In February 2020, we moved into our new school in Greenfield, purpose built especially for Bright Futures School and financed by local company Robert Scott and Son.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8">Our Facilities</h2>
    <p>
      The school is on one floor and consists of 16 dedicated classrooms. We have the capacity for 18 pupils. Our facilities include:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>16 individual pupil classrooms (each pupil has their own 1-1 space)</li>
      <li>Interactive sensory room</li>
      <li>Reception hub</li>
      <li>Staffroom and school office</li>
      <li>Shower room, utility area, and medical room</li>
      <li>Outdoor play space with sensory equipment</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-8">
      <img src="/images/school-exterior.jpg" alt="Bright Futures School exterior" class="rounded-lg w-full object-cover h-56" />
      <img src="/images/sensory-room.jpg" alt="Interactive sensory room" class="rounded-lg w-full object-cover h-56" />
    </div>

    <h2>Our Staff</h2>
    <p>
      Every pupil is supported by their own dedicated Learning Mentor. All Learning Mentors are overseen by qualified teaching staff. Our staff are trained in Relationship Development Intervention (R.D.I.) / guiding, and change their communication and interaction style to remove demands and reduce anxiety.
    </p>

    <h2>In Memory of Dixon Milburn</h2>
    <p>
      Bright Futures School honours the memory of Dixon Milburn, whose vision and dedication helped shape the school in its earliest years.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 flex gap-4 flex-wrap">
    <a href="/about/history" class="btn-outline">Our History</a>
    <a href="/about/overview" class="btn-outline">Overview &amp; Philosophy</a>
    <a href="/admissions" class="btn-primary">Admissions</a>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
